query.result:
124 “You are so close to the last salvation,” 125 began Beatrice, “that you ought to 126 have your lights clear and acute;
127 and therefore, before you are more immersed in it, 128 look down, and see how much world 129 under your feet already has been made for you;
130 so that your heart, as much as it can, joyful 131 presents itself to the triumphant throng 132 that happily comes through this round ether.”

